
"Close one huh?" Luke sheepishly grinned out. If I wasn't shaking so much from almost falling out of this thing I would have decked him in the face. Instead I glared at him and pulled myself onto my butt.
"I'll give you a twenty second head start for home when we land. You might want to seriously think about taking that offer." Luke's grin is wiped clean off his face. Fear is now washing over him along with guilt. We remained silent the rest of the way home.